1. what is blockchain       
blockchain is a Distributed database of immutable records called blocks, which are secured using cryptography.

i) blockchain are store data chronological order.
ii) once the data is recorded,it cannot be changed.               = means jab ek block dusre se jud gya to usme koye v changes aap ni kr skte ho.

2. A block is a record book which contains the details of transaction data.
- Every block is given,and aggregate set of transactions to be validted/verify/and edited to itself , 

3. So basically, A block consist of 4 details:-
i)  Hash of pervious block                                                        = It contains the "hash of pervious block"
ii) Transaction Data                                                              = It contains and aggregate list of transactions 
iii)Nonce                                                                         = It also contains the value of Nonce
iv)Hash                                                                           = and the hash for the block of itself,which is like of digital signature of the block

